Package gameinterfaces

Interface Monster

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Creature
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MyMonster
    public interface Monster
extends Creature
    A class that implements this interface should have the following attributes:
    • isEnraged: boolean
    • enrageThreshold: int
    The implementing class should only have the following constructor: public Monster(String name, String description, int hitPoints, int damage, int enrageThreshold)

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method Description
      boolean canEnrage()
      This method returns true if monster hitPoints falls below this.enrageThreshold.
      void enrage()
      This method will double this.damage for this Monster if it hasn't already been enraged.

      • Methods inherited from interface gameinterfaces.Creature

        attack, isAlive, takeDamage, toString

    • Method Detail

      • enrage

        void enrage()
        This method will double this.damage for this Monster if it hasn't already been enraged. In this case, this.isEnraged should be set to true. Otherwise, this method has no effect.

        This method will also display the message:

        "this.name has been enraged"

      • canEnrage

        boolean canEnrage()
        This method returns true if monster hitPoints falls below this.enrageThreshold.
        Returns:
        a boolean value indicating whether the monster can enrage.
